#Text=Chattanooga
#Text=Chattanooga is the 4th largest city in Tennessee .
#Text=It is the seat of Hamilton County .
#Text=It is in Southeast Tennessee on the Tennessee River and near the border of Georgia .
#Text=It is famous for being immortalized in the popular 1941 song Chattanooga Choo Choo , made famous by Glenn Miller .
#Text=Understand

#Text=Chattanooga played an important role during the American Civil War , when it was a major railroad hub and one of the most industrialized parts of the Confederacy along with the nearby city of Atlanta , resulting in Chattanooga and being at the center of numerous pitched battles .
#Text=Many of the tourist attractions center around Civil War history such as numerous battlefield parks in and around the city .

#Text=It is less prominent today because of the decline of its famed railroad , immortalized in the popular song Chattanooga Choo Choo , which is also commemorated in numerous tourist attractions and the popular Chattanooga Choo Choo hotel .
#Text=As of the census of 2000 , there are 155,554 people , 65,499 households , and 39,626 families residing in the city .
#Text=There are 72,108 housing units at an average density of 205.9/km² ( 533.3/mi² ) .
#Text=The racial makeup of the city is 59.71 % White , 36.06 % African American , 0.29 % Native American , 1.54 % Asian .
#Text=2.11 % of the population are Hispanic or Latino of any race .

#Text=Despite its economic loss and a small population , the city has become notably modernized , urbanized , and economically revitalized , receiving nationally recognition for the renaissance of its once-dilapidated , post-Industrial downtown and redevelopment of its riverfront .
#Text=Within the last ten years the city has won three national awards for outstanding " livability " , and nine Gunther Blue Ribbon Awards for excellence in housing and consolidated planning .
#Text=An early cornerstone of this project was the restoration of the historic Walnut Street Bridge , which is now the world 's longest pedestrian bridge .

#Text=Chattanooga is the corporate headquarters and home of Blue Cross & Blue Shield of Tennessee , Rock Creek Outfitters , Krystal , Chattem , Unum , The Chattanooga Bakery ( home of the Moon Pie ) , and Miller Industries , and the largest tow truck manufacturer in the world ( Chattanooga is the birthplace of the tow truck , so you 'll also find tourist attractions such as the tow truck museum to commemorate this ) .
#Text=Chattanooga is also home to the Tennessee Valley Authority , a self-funding government agency which operates numerous power plants in the South .

#Text=Following the city 's industrial decline , many businesses in the banking and insurance industries also set up operations in Chattanooga ; the city is home to large branch offices of Cigna , AT&T and UBS .
#Text=By car
#Text=I-75 ( North-South ) and I-24 ( East-West ) intersect in Chattanooga .
#Text=I-75 - Easy access from Atlanta and Knoxville .
#Text=Begins in Hialeah , Florida and ends in Sault Ste. Marie , Michigan at the Canadian border .
#Text=I-24 - Easy access from Murfreesboro , Nashville and Kentucky .
#Text=I-59 - Connects to I-24 just Southwest of Chattanooga , gives access to Birmingham , Alabama , Southeast Mississippi and ends near New Orleans .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Chattanooga Metropolitan Airport ( CHA ) ) ( The airport is located east of downtown Chattanooga and you can easily get transportation from the airport to local hotels ) .
#Text=It is serviced by : American Eagle ; Delta Connection Carriers ; Allegiant Air ( Nonstop service only to Orlando , Tampa , and Fort Lauderdale ; no onestops or connections ) .
#Text=There are non-stop flights to/from Chattanooga :
#Text=Atlanta , GA
#Text=Charlotte , NC
#Text=Chicago , IL ( Service to O'Hare International Airport )
#Text=Dallas , TX ( Service to Dallas-Ft . Worth International Airport )
#Text=Detroit , MI ( Service to Detroit Wayne County International Airport )
#Text=New York City , NY ( Service to LaGuardia Airport )
#Text=Orlando , FL ( Service to Orlando Sanford Airport )
#Text=Philadelphia , PA
#Text=Tampa Bay , FL ( Service to St. Petersburg/Clearwater Airport )
#Text=Washington , D.C. ( Service to Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport , otherwise known as National Airport , and Dulles Airport )
#Text=By bus
#Text=Greyhound , 960 Airport Rd , ☏ +1-800-231-2222 .
#Text=Service to Chattanooga begins and ends at their station found near the airport .
#Text=To get downtown from Greyhound walk a couple blocks to Van Ness Rd & Lee Hwy and catch the inbound CARTA route 4 bus to downtown .
#Text=Last stop is at Market St. & W 4th Ave.
#Text=Megabus ( The bus stop is located on Market Street at West 14th Street , next to the Chattanooga Choo Choo . ) .
#Text=Service from Atlanta , Nashville , Knoxville , Lexington , Louisville , Cincinnati , Columbus , Cleveland , Indianapolis , and Chicago
#Text=By boat
#Text=Chattanooga is accessible by way of the Tennessee River by personal water craft .
#Text=Ross 's Landing ( downtown Chattanooga ) .
#Text=There are 11 mooring posts with electrical and water hookups .
#Text=Chickamauga Marina , Chickamauga Lake at the Chickamauga Dam , Kings Point Rd , ☏ +1423 622-1978 .
#Text=Summer , May 1 - Sept 30 , Su - Th 8:30AM – 6:30PM and F - Sa 8:30AM-7PM ; Winter , Oct 1 - Apr 30 , M - Su 8:30AM – 5:30PM .
#Text=Full service marina , complete with laundry/bath house .
#Text=Fuel Dock/Ships Store open 7 days year round accepting all major credit cards .
#Text=Gold Point Yacht Harbor ( just off the Tennessee River at mile marker 472 ) , ☏ +1423 622-1978 .
#Text=Constructed in 2001 and nestled into a picturesque cove .
#Text=All business for Gold Point Yacht Harbor is conducted from the marina office located at the Chickamauga Marina .

#Text=Shady Grove Harbor , 1805 Clift Eldridge Rd , Soddy Daisy ( To get to the harbor , enter the Soddy Creek Channel at Mile Marker 487 , then travel 1.3 miles up Soddy Creek . ) , ☏ +1423 332-5613 .
#Text=Summer ( Apr 1 - Labor Day ) open 7 days 8AM-8PM ; Winter , F - Tu 10AM-6PM. .
#Text=The Ship Store is equipped to satisfy all boating needs .
#Text=Island Cove Marina and Resort , Mile marker 477.5 on the Tennessee River , 6701 Highway 58 , Harrison , ☏ +1423 344-8331 , fax : +1423 344-6275 .
#Text=Ship Store hours : Summer , M - Sa 8AM-6PM , Su 9AM-6PM ; Winter , M - Sa 8AM-5PM , Su 10AM-5PM. .
#Text=Featuring a full stocked ship store , transient dockage , bath house , laundry and a 24 hour fuel dock .
#Text=They were awarded a 5 Anchor Rating by Quimby 's Cruise Guide .
#Text=Sydney 's On the River restaurant also on site .
